In a letter left at his apartment in Henry County, Ga., Barton acknowledged that the murders of his family were similar to the Alabama killings, in which police believe the victims were killed with a hatchet.
In a note left in the Stockbridge apartment where he killed his family, Barton wrote that he planned to live just long enough to kill ... the people that greedily sought my destruction.
In a note left for authorities, Barton said he killed Leigh Ann on Tuesday and placed her body in a closet of her Stockbridge apartment.
